Additionally, the paper discusses the relationship between CCG and other mildly context-sensitive grammars, which is a topic of interest in computational linguistics.

The paper may also be relevant to the sub-category of machine learning (cs.LG) because it discusses the use of parsing algorithms for CCG, which could potentially involve machine learning techniques. 

The sub-category of artificial intelligence (cs.AI) is also a possibility because CCG is a formalism used in natural language understanding, which is a key area of research in AI. 

The paper's focus on parsing algorithms and worst-case time complexity suggests that it may also be relevant to the sub-category of data structures and algorithms (cs.DS). 

Finally, the paper's discussion of the relationship between CCG and other grammars may make it relevant to the sub-category of systems and control (cs.SY), which includes research on formal languages and automata theory.
